ionaire Elon Musk seems to have found a new favorite federal judge: Reed =
=0AO=E2=80=99Connor in Fort Worth, Texas.=0A=0AMusk=E2=80=99s social media =
company X has filed two major lawsuits against groups he =0Asees as antagon=
ists, and O=E2=80=99Connor is presiding over both of them, even though =0An=
one of the parties is based in Texas.=0A=0ASo far, O=E2=80=99Connor has del=
ivered stunningly pro-Musk decisions, which have =0Agained widespread atten=
tion.=0A=0ARight, I mean, in some sense this is unfair, but that=E2=80=99s =
the system=E2=80=99s fault, =0Anot Musk=E2=80=99s. He gets to choose where =
to bring the lawsuits, and it would be =0Asomewhat silly of him to bring th=
em in anunfriendly court. If you get to pick =0Athe judge, pick the one who=
