ightly too pro-Musk. The Verge reports =0A<https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/=
13/24219740/texas-judge-reed-oconnor-tesla-stock-x-antitrust-lawsuit>=0A:=
=0A=0AA Texas judge who was assigned two cases involving Elon Musk=E2=80=99=
s X platform has =0Arecused himself from one of them, shortly after a repor=
t that he owns stock in =0ATesla.=0A=0AUS District Court Judge Reed O=E2=80=
=99Connor was assigned to X=E2=80=99s recent antitrust =0Alawsuit against a=
dvertisers over their boycott of the service, as well as a =0Aseparate case=
 against Media Matters, which the company sued for a report =0Ashowing that=
 X displayed ads from major brands next to pro-Nazi content. On =0ATuesday,=
 O=E2=80=99Connor filed a notice to the court clerk recusing himself from t=
he =0Aantitrust lawsuit. He still appears to be assigned to the Media Matte=
rs case as =0Aof Tuesday afternoon.=0A=0AThe recusal came just a few days a=
fter NPR reported on O=E2=80=99Connor=E2=80=99s Tesla stock =0Aholdings, wh=
ich, according to a financial disclosure, fall between $15,001 and =0A$50,0=
00. Musk, of course, is Tesla=E2=80=99s CEO.=0A=0AAhahahaha oops. My Bloomb=
erg Opinion colleague Noah Feldman writes =0A<https://www.bloomberg.com/opi=
nion/articles/2024-08-14/tesla-stock-should-disqualify-judge-in-both-elon-m=
usk-x-lawsuits=3Fcmpid=3DBBD081424_MONEYSTUFF&utm_medium=3Demail&utm_source=
=3Dnewsletter&utm_term=3D240814&utm_campaign=3Dmoneystuff>=0A:=0A=0AThe Cod=
e of Judicial Conduct says judges may not preside over cases that would =0A=
affect a company in which they own shares. Because X and Tesla are legally =
=0Aseparate entities, O=E2=80=99Connor perhaps initially believed that this=
 rule did not =0Aapply here.=0A=0ABut there is another, broader rule in the=
 same judicial ethics code. That rule =0Asays that a judge =E2=80=9Cshall d=
isqualify himself=E2=80=9D if his =E2=80=9Cimpartiality might =0Areasonably=
 be questioned.=E2=80=9D The basic idea is that a judge should recuse himse=
lf =0Aif a reasonable person in possession of the relevant facts would beli=
eve that =0Athe judge has reason for bias. And there is good reason to thin=
k that this rule =0Acovers O=E2=80=99Connor.=0A=0AWhat a bummer for Musk. T=
he job is to choose a judge who (1) will be biased in =0Ayour favor but (2)=
 won=E2=80=99tseem biased in your favor under judicial ethics rules.=0A=0A=
